<h3>About the ACM(lul)</h3>
     	<p>We are more than a computer club on campus, we are a campus
organization with affiliation to the Association for Computing Machinery</p>
	<ul><li>Our purpose is to increase awareness and usage of technology with
an emphasis on computing technology (hardware, software, operating
systems, etc).</li><li>The BC ACM is made up of students from different majors, so any student can join.</li><li>Activities include social events (pizza party!) and ModFest (showing off modded computers).</li><li>Software activities include: Workshops on programming languages and Web Design</li><li>September and October are spent getting ready for the programming competition.</li><li>Each year three teams from Bridgewater go to the ACM competition in October.</li><li>The BC-ACM lab also supports advanced classes in Computer Science,
senior seminar projects for Computer Science majors, and senior seminar
projects for Information Systems Management majors.</li></ul>
      <h3>Joining the Bridgewater Student Chapter of the ACM</h3>
Joining our chapter is simple, just come to one of the meetings.<br>
If you don't know when one is you can e-mail <a href="mailto:rschneid@bridgewater.edu">Ray Schneider</a>, or one of our
officers.<table border="0" width="100%"><tbody><tr>
